It provides standardized biomedical concept relations and synonyms (Humphreys et al.1998). The UMLS has been widely used in many natural language processing tasks, including information retrieval (Eichmann et al.1998), extraction (Rindflesch et al.2000), and text summarization (Elhadad et al.2004; Fiszman et al.2004). The UMLS includes the Metathesaurus (MT), which contains over one million biomedical concepts and the Semantic Network (SN), which represents a high-level abstraction from the UMLS Metathesaurus.
